    oakcurric:thread-bq04-biology-why-are-there-similarities-and-differences-between-living-things .

oakcurric:unit-110
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Healthy me"@en ;
  curric:slug "healthy-me" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers the importance of exercise, balanced nutrition, and hygiene for
  humans. It involves performing simple tests, observing closely, and identifying and
  classifying information. Emphasis is on asking questions, using observations to suggest
  answers, and gathering and recording data."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' prior learning from Human body parts, where
  they learned to identify and name basic parts of the body and their functions. In Healthy me,
  pupils will explore the importance of exercise, nutrition, and hygiene for keeping their
  bodies healthy. This prepares them for the next unit, Healthy eating, where they will deepen
  their understanding of how a balanced diet contributes to overall health and the body's
  nutritional needs for growth and development.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-110-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-110-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-110-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-110-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-110-5 ;
  curric:id "110"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.537715Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-biology-key-stage-1 ,
    natcurric:scheme-the-sciences-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-bq05-biology-how-do-living-things-stay-healthy .

oakcurric:unit-111
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Uses of everyday materials"@en ;
  curric:slug "uses-of-everyday-materials" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores identifying and comparing the suitability of everyday materials
  like wood, metal, and plastic for specific uses. It examines how solid objects' shapes can
  change by squashing, bending, twisting, and stretching. The focus is on simple tests, and
  using data to answer questions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' prior learning from Everyday materials, where
  they learned to identify materials and describe their properties. In Uses of everyday
  materials, pupils will explore how different materials are suited for specific tasks based on
  their characteristics. This prepares them for the next unit, Introduction to states of matter
  and changing states, where they will learn about solids, liquids, and gases, deepening their
  understanding of how materials can change form under different conditions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-111-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-111-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-111-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-111-4 ;
  curric:id "111"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.939069Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-chemistry-key-stage-1 ,
    natcurric:scheme-physics-key-stage-1 ,
    natcurric:scheme-the-sciences-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-physics-why-do-materials-have-different-properties ,
    oakcurric:thread-bq08-chemistry-how-can-substances-be-made-and-changed ,
    oakcurric:thread-bq07-chemistry-what-are-things-made-of .

